	the new standards of luxury - shame on the burj al arab	I am an hotel owner (with good ranking on tripadvisor) and a good traveller.I must say that never in my life I have found such a combination of style, luxury and service. The staff is simply amazing, Anuj at the Sloanes restaurant or the bar manager at the 44 floor club just to mention a couple of people but everyone is simply extraordinary, working hard, efficient and always with a smile even in difficult busy times. Try to ask for directions for example, they will not give them to you...they will walk you there whatever they are doing !The best breakfast, rich and elegant. The bar at 44th floor is a lively elegant place with cheap drinks (about 50 dirhams for a Martini with an astonishing view). My room is the best room I have ever had. The indego restaurant is elegant and charming....Just a note to make a comparison. To visit the world famours Burj Al Arab I went there for a drink on the Sky bar. The only thing worth was the view. The lobby is tacky, without any sense of style and elegance, nothing to note at the bar in term of service not a nice glass or knife.... cheap stuff everywhere with some gold here and there...I think it is just a a marketing miracle. Same think for the Jumeirah beach hotel we went to visit. Cheap and without any sense of style. Thank God we were staying in Grosvenor and not in the Burj....for a fraction of the price.... Another note...try to go to the amazing Buddah bar of the Grosvenor and compare it to the Burj Al Arab...Budda bar definite winner. Congratulations to the marketers of the Burj Al Arab and to the wonderful people that makes the Grosvenor house a truly amazing place !	
	"THE" place to stay in Dubai	Don't be put off by the talk of building noise at the marina......you'd find it difficult to find somewhere in Dubai where they aren't building. The rooms are very sound proof and why would would you want to stay by the hotel pool when you can use all the facilities and beach at the Royal Meridien which is just round the corner? Not that the pool isn't lovely but it's in the middle of a very built up area. We checked in at 8.30am and were given a room straight away which is virtually unheard of in other hotels.....AND were given an upgrade to a suite. It was absolutely perfect......the beds are HUGE and sooooooo comfy.Breakfast is quite an experience......it could take a while to try out everything on offer - so make sure you arrive early!! They don't stop serving till 11am which is another bonus - you are on holiday after all. With the peace and quiet, the most comfortable beds in the world and black out linings you're likely to sleep in ....a real treat for parents away from the children!We booked a room with club lounge access which was another bonus......lovely surroundings and great drinks.....shop around and you should find an inclusive rate.This is isn't a cheap hotel ....but from research seemed the best value for money for what's on offer in Dubai. The attention to detail really makes this hotel stand out.They seem to have thought of everything.	
	The best 5 star hotel I have stayed in...however...	Problem number one.. the Hotel is bang in the middle of at least three other construction sites. There is significant noise during the day and into the evening and you could not sit on your balcony or around the pool area without encountering serious construction noise. So,if you are at all concerned about the noise then you should choose their sister Hotel Le Meridien Spa which is situated right on the beach and has the most fantastic gardens, pool and beach area that you are ever likely to encounter. As mentioned previously, should you choose the GH, there is a very efficient shuttle which takes you to Le Meridien Resort.The facilities are extremely good there and you are treated as a guest of the hotel.Problem number two... There isn't one..Grosvenor House is the best 5 star hoteI I have stayed in. It is absolutely superb. From the minute you step out of the car to visit GH you are met with friendly efficient staff who are all absolutely fantastic. We expected to wait for our room as we arrived there at around 8.30am. However, the check in procedure is flawless and you are served tea, soft drinks and pastries until your room is ready. We took the advice of fellow trip advisors and booked a club room. These are situated from around the 30th floor upwards and we had a very nice balcony view across the marina to the sea and The Palm. The rooms are very spacious and well appointed. It appeared that every time we went out, your room was cleaned. Fresh towels were placed in the room three times a day and the housekeeping in general was once again the best I have come across.We had the opportunity to visit Rhodes Mezzanine Restaurant, which must be very close to the best restaurant in Dubai. Service is very good, the food superb. We had a meal at the Burj Al Arab and I have to say that, in my opinion, Rhodes was better.We also experienced a visit to Indigo, their Indian Restaurant, and again, this was the best Indian meal you are ever likely to experience.Breakfast was again superb and it is difficult to keep finding superlatives for this hotel. There was everything from an egg chef, a pancake chef, sushi, fresh fruit, pastries, meats, cereals, up to a full english breakfast.All in all, having stayed at many five star hotels, I have to say that this must be nearer six star. The hotel is very difficult to fault in any area.Highly recommended.	
