h visit as soon as possible.	
Nov 8 2009 	A Shacky Start But Recovered Well....	We arrived around 5.30am, collected luggage and went to find our driver (part of the hotel package included transfers) out of all the hotels only ours was missing - we located him a few minutes later and where soon on our way....We were in the hotel 1/2 hour later, it then took an hour to organise our room key, we were asked to take a seat and then a lot of toing and froing took place, between us and the counter (the hotel knew our expected time of arrival several months earlier). They would ask for a credit card, this would then be taken away and then brought back to sign some 10 mins later. After a 9 hour overnight flight from Cape Town a little more efficiency would have been nice.The first room we were allocated a Club Room on the 39th floor had the most spectacular view of The Palm, what made it unacceptable was the smell of cigarettes, so strong you could taste them - as non smokers this was never going to be acceptable. After explaining this to reception we then waited nearly another hour in this room for them to organise a replacement. The new room was an upgrade to a one bedroom suite and was lovely. Again, efficiency was lacking as it took another 40 minutes and a phone call from my husband to chase our luggage. At this point we'd been in the hotel for 2 1/2 hours. Just as we were getting to sleep we had a phone call to see how the room was..... We gave up and went to the pool....The good news is from this point everything got better, the hotel is very stylish, the room was great and the service was spot on. The Guest Service desk was helpful and booked a couple of trips for us, both of which we really enjoyed. We ate in 2 restaurants including the Buhda Bar - a real treat. We had access to the Club Lounge which we used twice for evening drinks, the choice of canapés was good as were the drinks. The service in here was exceptionally good.A lot is written about the construction work in Dubai and yes it’s all true!!!! That said our room was quiet and we used the beach club in the other hotel so we were not really bothered by it.	
Nov 3 2009 	Superb in every respect	Having previously stayed twice at the Royal Meridien, we decided to book at the Grosvenor House this time, as it was half term and we thought it would be the quieter option. After the wonderful welcome at the airport, we were delighted as soon as we stepped into the lobby. The GH is so stylish and elegant, with marble floors and relaxing decor, unlike many of the hotels in Dubai which are very garish! The floral arrangements are simply fantastic. We had a one bedroom apartment, 1416, which was on the side of the hotel, with views of the marina and also across to the Royal Meridien and the sea. The building work is mainly at the front of the hotel so it was very quiet. The apartment was lovely, bedroom, kitchen, sitting/dining room and a separate toilet. The staff who serviced the room did a wonderful job - great supply of clean towels and toiletries and we very much appreciated the fruit and cake which arrived daily. We were there for six nights and had dinner four times in the hotel - Indego, Sloanes twice and Buddha Bar. All were of a very high standard, and one night in Sloanes, the chef made a chicken curry especially for us. Wonderful! One night we ate out at Frankies, the restaurant on The Walk which belongs to Marco Pierre White &amp; Frankie Dettori - this is highly recommended, though I am sure you need to book. Food absolutely fantastic, although there are two sittings - 7.30 &amp; 9.30. The remaining night we went to the Indian themed night at the LRM Brasserie, as we had been to that on our previous visits. This turned out to be rather disappointing, after the food at GH, with not a great selection of meat curries, although several vegetable ones.The Club Lounge deserves special mention. The afternoon tea and the canapes (which are different every night) are truly superb. The staff are so attentive and we would like to especially thank Swapnil in the Club Lounge who looked after us so well. He always seemed to be on duty and when we asked him about his days off, he just said that he loved his job. The views from the Lounge across to the Palm are breathtaking, especially during the day. Well worth asking to go outside on the balcony to take some photos.We went over to the beach at the Royal Meridien where the staff were great in sorting out umbrellas and sunbeds and regularly bringing cold towels, water sprays &amp; smoothies. There is so much space that is no problem to find somewhere that suits you, whether that is sun or shade, beach or grass.All in all, a wonderful week and we will certainly be returning to GH, rather than the Royal Meridien, which is more family orientated. With children, LRM would be an excellent choice, but for couples, GH every time!	
Nov 2 2009 	Superb hotel with great service	We have just got back from spending a significant aniiversary at GH, and the staff there made us feel very special. If your budget runs to one of the Club Rooms then go for it - access to the Club Lounge on the 44th floor is well worth it - the afternoon tea is wonderful and the limo transfer to and from the airport is very efficient! Our room on the 37th floor had breathtaking and uninterrupted views of The Palm, Burj Al Arab, etc. But hurry if you want this as GH's second tower is going up right in front and will eventually obscure views from the old part of the hotel. Others on here also mention the building work - even from 37 floors up the 24 hour working could be heard through the well glazed windows, though it didn't particularly bother us.The staff are GH's main asset - friendly, helpful and always smiling. What a great team.We particularly enjoyed breakfast on the outside terrace at Sloane's - only possible though when the temperatures dip towards and through winter. We also enjoyed the beach at the Royal Meridien - the shuttle from GH is easy and efficient - but who ARE those people who cover the loungers with towels at an unearthly hour??? There's room for everyone, so chill out!The location of the hotel is good, and will be better when the walkways around the Marina are complete. Taxis are cheap and access to Dubai Mall takes around 20 minutes in good traffic, the Creek in 30 minutes. So for beach and city access, GH is great. GH lives up to its name as a 5 star hotel for service, style and comfort. In spite of the very minor issues mentioned above we would most definitely stay there again. There are many young pretenders in the Dubai hotel stakes, but GH still beats them all!	
Nov 1 2009 	Great Hotel	We picked the hotel based on the reviews on Tripadvisor. We were not disapointed. We stayed in a club room and were picked up by a white Lexus from the airport. We would recomend a club room as it gets you a better room and access to the club louge. The hotel is very well laid out with very good restaurants and bars. There are number of great bars particularly bar 44 at the top of the hotel which has great views and lovely cocktails.The budda bar is well worth a visit although it is rather expensive for the standard of food. We have eaten in a number of michelin star restaurants and the food is not to that standard but is a similar price.The staff were excellent and extremely friendly. They could not do enoiugh to help. The hotel is very well decorated and guests are encouraged to be smartly dressed which adds to the ambiance. There is a shuttle bus to the beach which takes about 5 mins at the sister hotel, Le Meridian. The beach is beautiful and staff come round with cold towels and sorbe. The water is like a bath and there are life guards on view at all times.There is a lot of building work but it did not bother us as we used taxis everywhere. At night we also did not notice the noise being on the 37th floor plus the beds are extremely comfortable.Overal a great hotel where you can relax and enjoy Dubai. Dubai itself is not cheap but it is well worth a visit. Afternoon tea at the Burj is a real treat but I would not stay there. The Grosvner is understated whilst the Burj is just bling!	
