Sep 28 2009 	Did I Stay Somewhere Else?!?	Stopped here for an overnight stay on our return from the Maldives. We choose this property mainly due to the good reviews on here and a bad experience during our last visit to Dubai at the Jumeriah Beach.Firstly, let me point out that we have been very fortunate to stayin many &quot;5 star&quot; hotels over the last few years (see other reviews) and so would like to think we have good experience to draw upon when writing these reviews.We had booked a Club Executive Room via the hotels own website and got a very good price although the website and information on the room tyep was very poor (ie not immediatley apparent I had booked a smoking room, no mention of airport transfers or other club executive priveleges). I had to fire off several emails and make one phone call to Dubai before departure to make sure airport transfers were included and to book ours. Despite this, the staff I did eventually deal with will freindly and professional at all times. Upon arrival we were upgraded to a suite although I strongly suspect this was because the hotel was at 100% occupancy. As nice as this was, it did mean a room on a lower level which was more prone to the buliding noise from next door....the main reason we had booked a club room! Luckily the end of Ramadan celebrations meant public holidays and therefore no construction (or noise) during our stay. The suite was of a comfortable size but did not have a balcony, the TV remote was threadbare / not working and a handle on the cupboard fell of as soon as I touched it.......not very inspiring. There was no information in the room regarding the executive/club lounge and so we had to call Guest relations to figure out the &quot;protocol&quot; for the evening canapes/drinks.The room entitled me to use of the free in room broadband internet although this was extremely slow and tempremental....no good if you were visiting on businessWe used the pool area to refresh ourselves after our flight and found it very average.....average size pool, average service, below average view. We then retired to the 44th floor for drinks/canapes and found that the club lounge was (unsuprisingly due to the occupancy) full and we had to be moved to another area of the bar itself which was still very nice and had good service.We ordered room service rather than eat out as the main purpose of our visit was a restful nights sleep. The food was mediorce at best.....cold chips, nachos looking like they'd simply been blitzed in the microwave with a lump of cheese on top.Worse was to come when we went down for breakfast.....the hotel seemed to have been transported from the Costa Del Sol.....hoards of english tourists in trunks, t-shirts and sandles and a queue to be let into the dining area (Sloanes). I appreciate this is one of the busiest times of year and that buliding works means low rates, less &quot;business&quot; types and more &quot;tourists&quot; but at this point the Grosvenor House certainly did not live up to it's 5 star reputation! The queue was badly managed and we were seated after approx 10 minutes (I think we were moved forward due to being in a Club room which was nice for us but not for those still waiting when we finished 20 minutes later). The buffet, although expansive, was very low quality and again, due to the high occupancy queues for hot food were long, staff were visibly harrassed and we left after a quick pastry and what ever cold meats we could get our hands on!All in all then, a very dissapointing visit which has tarnished our view of Dubai even more. I think we were unlucky to visit when we did but given our overall experience I don't think this hotel warrants being either 5 star, or 4th in Dubai......of course many others, the vast majority in fact seem to disagree but all I would say is look at their past reviews and judge for yourself who you may choose to believe......If you want a cheap but relatively &quot;nice&quot; hotel in Dubai and aren't put off by hoards off holidaymakers, building works or having to get a bus to the beach then this maybe the hotel for you. If you want class, style, good service, business facilities and 5 star then look elsewhere	
Sep 28 2009 	BEST HOTEL STAY... EVER!	Just got back from Dubai, and although I'm usually months behind with posting reviews, the Grosvenor deserves the special attention it afforded us over the last three days! We booked about a month ago, and my partner emailed the hotel to explain we were celebrating a special occasion to see if they could offer us anything to celebrate.We didn't get much of a confirmation back so weren't expecting anything, but upon arrival we had been upgraded to a one bedroom suite!The suite had two bathrooms, dining area and fully fitted out kitchen, including dishwasher! that put our two bed apartment in Leeds to shame! The views were fantastic and the service truly exceptional.Many amenities are at the sister hotel, but the Grosvenor does have its own pool and spa - we enjoyed a 'Rasool' (sp) mud treatment that only cost around £45 each and was well worth it.The only let down in the hotel was Indego restaurant - supposedly overseen by Vineet Bhatia, the overpriced food resembled a Morrisons takeaway for two - not what we expected from such a great chef! Must be aimed at people with little experience in Indian food, but as someone who has lived within walking distance of the best Indian restaurants in the West Mids and Yorkshire, this was a disappointment.As we only had a three night stay, we didn't get chance to try the other restaurants, but room service is a must - very reasonably priced and massive portions. Breakfast was also fantastic, so don't let my Indego comments put you off - this truly is the best hotel I have ever stayed in - No. 1 of well over 200 across four continents so please give it a try if you're staying in Dubai!Couple of general tips - try Tagine at the Royal Mirage - beautiful food; make time for a trip to Wild Wadi Water Park - but don't hire towels - at £4 each they are just not needed, in the heat you are dry before you get back in a taxi!Overall, we will definitely be going back to Dubai, and definitely staying at The Grosvenor again - well done guys!!	
