d. The drinks are of a reasonable price, and made really well by the very friendly bar staff. Service was first rate.We had our breakfast at Sloanes, and it really has to be experienced. I have never had so much choice when it comes to having breakfast. The waiting staff were efficient and friendly, and anything that was finished with was removed from the table in a timely but discrete manner.There was a lot of building work going on around the hotel, this didn’t bother me personally, but I could see why it would bother some people. If building work does bother you, a holiday to Dubai is not recommended. It is everywhere. I would wait a couple of years when it has moved on. We had no problems walking the perimeter of the hotel and part of the marina, although it is a bit bare. I hope that when building work finishes there will be some gardening involved to add some much needed greenery.Overall, I cannot rate this hotel highly enough. I have stayed in hotels all over the world, and this one is by far and away my favourite. It is the level of service that sets it apart from other hotels. I lost my mobile phone in a taxi, the hotel security found it within an hour and I had it back within two. All the staff were fantastic, and they made my wife and I feel almost like we were the only guests staying at the hotel. I will most definitely be coming back for a return visit.	
