Aug 24 2009 	Dubai Oasis	Let's get the negative out of the way first - the Dubai Marina is a &quot;work in progress&quot; and is likely to be so for some time. This means construction work, and plenty of it. Having said that, you can avoid this by a) getting a room on a high floor and b) no expecting to walk around at street level (which is frankly unrealistic in Dubai anyway). Also the internet is a bit too slow for work purposes.Onto the positives - the staff deserve a special mention. They were universally polite, friendly, enthusiastic and professional. Special mention goes to the Guest Services who handled every request with care and aplomb. The building itself is of a very high standard and the 45th floor Club Room is an excellent place to relax with a drink. If you had to pick a failing it would be that the pool is a tad cramped. Luckily the Grosvenor shares (very good) facilities with the (beach front) Maridien Grand which is 5mins by shuttle. Lastly the room, we were on the 35th floor which was high enough to not be bothered by the construction noise. The view over the Palm is awesome but likely to be obscured by the new tower going up next door, but for now it's top notch. Interior fittings were modern and tasteful, and size-wise the room and bathroom would count as a mini-suite in New York or London. Especially liked the little touches like the evening snacks left by housekeeping.All in all a fantastic hotel to stay in - the staff, the atmosphere and the quality of the service make it a real oasis of calm in a crazy city. Already looking forward to the next time.	
