Aug 13 2009 	Wonderful hotel with only one (temporary) flaw	We stayed at the Grosvenor House in Dubai for the first week in August. It was practically perfect - gorgeous room with every luxury you could wish for, delightful staff who couldn't do enough for you, wonderful beach, helpful and knowledgeable concierge service, the best room service we'd ever tasted... I could go on and on! The only problem (and it's a temporary one) is that the hotel is currently surrounded by a building site. They are building an identical hotel building next to the existing one, and it's still in the early stages so a while go yet. Although the noise from the work didn't particularly bother us (we were on the 27th floor so too high up to hear much), it meant that it was literally impossible to walk anywhere outside the hotel. There was no way out by foot at all. Even to get to the beach (over the road) you had to take a shuttle. We really missed not being able to pop out for an evening stroll, but having to take taxis everywhere.I would still recommend the hotel - once inside it was everything you could want from a five star establishment and more. But if you're the sort of people who would hate being dependent on motorised transport to get anywhere from your hotel room, look elsewhere, at least until the building work is finished. Also, book a room on a high floor to escape the building noise.	
