Jul 27 2009 	Absolutely Amazing - Stop trying to decide just book here!	We went to Dubai for 4 days on our way to the Maldives. Our reason for the trip was our honeymoon, so we wanted something nice in Dubai. Problem was, there were so many options! We also considered the Address, Atlantis, Al Murooj Rotana. Finally, we just settled on Grosvenor House, and truthfully, the decision was quite arbitrary. We found a great deal and figured, what the heck? We in no way regret being so impulsive!The staff is superb. Checking in was a breeze. We relaxed in the lobby with ginger iced tea while they filled everything out for us. We were upgraded to the 41st floor with a HUGE balcony. As we were escorted to our room (at 8:30 am...early check in was so great after two long flights!), we mentioned that being on our honeymoon, the upgrade was an extra treat. Well, they didn't stop there! When we got back from breakfast, a bottle of champagne was waiting for us. That was very nice and unexpected.The staff went above and beyond for us. The hotel was certainly not at capacity, but literally everyone we ran into knew us and our comings and goings...this may seem weird, but the attention was nice. They took care of every reservation for us. In fact, we wanted to book a desert safari with some friends in town. They even coordinated pick up for our friends at their own hotel! We received friendly reminders and confirmations for everything they coordinated. They were just 150% on top of everything, and we must have called them at least a dozen times, so we gave them plenty of opportunity to be less than perfect. They never let us down.One thing that stood out was their assistance in my own negligence. On our way to Verre for dinner, I left my camera in the taxi. Verre was quite kind in assisting us and calling the cab companies, but we still mentioned my oversight to the desk upon arrival. Literally seconds after we entered our room, the head of security was there asking more questions. They reviewed the security tape, and the next day, my camera was back in hand. I thought for sure I was out of luck, and I think that would have been my fate if we stayed elsewhere. After that, every time we got into a taxi the doorman would hand us a card with our taxi number written on it, &quot;in case we left something.&quot; Embarrassing? Yes. But honestly very helpful and nice of them to remember to do each time.We ate at Buddha Bar, which was surprisingly delicious. The one in NYC is really more a club and not known for it's food, but the sushi platter here was quite notable. The service was also great, and the maitre d' brought us a personal message from our friend who had called while we were dining. The restaurant was very busy, so it was nice of them to do this.In terms of the facilities, the rooms are very comfortable, and the bathroom is gorgeous. The lobby is also quite lovely. The little treats each day were a wonderful snack. To touch upon construction...yes, you are surrounded by it. But the fact of the matter is that ALL of Dubai is surrounded by construction, so this should not deter you from selecting Grosvenor House. In fact, I guarantee wherever you stay you will feel surrounded by dust and cranes and bulldozers.As I mentioned, we got a great deal on the hotel, but we never felt like second class citizens for paying less than the prime rate. (our resort in the Maldives, however, made us feel that way for not selecting their ocean villa but opting for a beach retreat, so I know this happens.) Instead, Grosvenor House's priority was top notch service, and they delivered this every second of our stay. My husband and I travel frequently, and this was definitely the best hotel we have ever been to. We were blown away, and if we ever return to Dubai, we will book Grosvenor House without looking elsewhere at all, regardless of whether or not deals are available to us.	
