an Themed shopping centre, a bit like the Luxor in Vegas Emirates Mall - twice the size of bluewater and great for bargains Dubai Mall - the biggest shopping centre you will ever see, would take a few days to visit all the shops and cafes Gold Souk - crazy assed place people trying to sell you fake watches and bags everywhere, they are harmless, the gold shops are a total rip off mind, but have to be seen !!! Spice Souk, another crazy place, worth a look. Taxi's - dont hire a car its pointless, taxis (with petrol at 22p a litre, yes thats 22p) are dirt cheap, the longest ride we had was 30 mins to the Gold Zouk, cost ? £14 !!!! Restaurants we visited with prices Habtoor Grand Steak House - outstanding steaks !!! bill was £80 for 2 with beers Habtoor Grand - The Underground Pub - Great for sports and cheap food, 2 mains and 4 pints £50 with the football on Buddha Bar at The Grosvenor House - fantastic ambience, really good food, although keep this to yourselves, the starters on the menu are part of the canape selection you get in the club lounge ;-) and mighty fine they are too !!!! Nobu at the Atlantis - a wallet smashing £370 with wine, but wow, if you know your way around their menu, they do it well.... we feasted !!! Persian Restaurant at The Madinat - fantastic meat dishes didnt eat for 24 hours after this place, £80 for 2 with beers and starters Carluccios in Dubai Mall - 2 mains 2 fruit juices 1 starter to share £50 Fatburger in Dubai Mall - if you have ever been to IN n OUT in LA then this is the same !!!! fantastic burgers !!! 2 of us ate for £8 each with drinks all in all a fantastic holiday, didnt want to come home, will we be returning ? oh yes.... 1000000000% and we will ONLY stay at the Grosvenor House !!! Thanks to all the staff at this hotel you are ALL wonderful and a credit to your hotel, you are the reason this hotel is justifiably No1 in Dubai on TA Mark your staff are a credit to you, you should be proud !!	
