May 11 2009 	Nice facilities but average service and erratic Internet access	I just come back from a long weekend in Dubai and I stayed at the Grosvenor House. Having read the excellent reviews on TripAdvisor, I had high expectations but unfortunately, the hotel did not live up to its reputation for me.On the plus side:* Nice, modern and spotless hotel facilities. We stayed in room 3504 (a normal room, not a club room), which featured a nice terrace with views over the Palm Jumeirah and the Burj al Arab. Beware though, there is construction work going on 24/7 so it is quite noisy when you're on the terrace or when the window is open. Large comfy bed. Remote control for lighting and air conditioning is a nice high-tech touch although not so convenient to use in practice. Construction is going on all around the hotel so you need a taxi wherever you want to go but they're available any time and are cheap (max 20 UAD to any place in Jumeirah, 50 UAD if you go to Deira).* Access to Royal Meridien Beach through a good shuttle service every 15 min from 7am till 2am. Nice wide clean beach with good bar (try the lobster tails, they're excellent). Water is not very clean however, with some coke cans and other garbage floating. Nothing dramatic but do not expect clean turquoise waters over there. I'm not sure whether that's better in other parts of Dubai. Water temperature was about 27-30°. * Beautiful lobby with fresh flowers. You get one of the flowers on your pillow during the turn down service.* Breakfast is what you expect from a 5 star hotel with a good choice and good quality.On the minus side:* The hotel advertises free broadband internet (note: through cable, not WIFI) but it did not work for me. I could only access it every day around 20:00 for 1/2 hour. The rest of the time I got an error message: 'Invalid parameter string. Please contact the administrator'. Despite several people of the staff coming to my room and trying to solve the issue, they could not fix it. The manager on duty had an easy conclusion: &quot;there must be a problem with your computer&quot;... I use this computer every day, travel professionally a lot and use this computer to access Internet in many other hotels and never had a single issue... The manager on duty promised me to check again what they could do but he never came back to me... Good intentions but no results. Bottom line: if you need an hotel with a reliable internet access, chose another place. * We arrived at the hotel on the first day around 7am. I had booked a room for the previous night as they could not guarantee an early check-in and I wanted to be sure I could get some rest after a night flight. We left the hotel at around 14:00 and left the 'Please service my room' sign at the door. Coming back at 18:00, the room was still not serviced. I called the guest services and left for dinner. When we came back the room was done but there was no drinking water and some amenities had not been replaced. While I've been charged for a full night, what we got was nothing more than a turn down service... They brought us the water after I called them but still this is not what I expect from a 5 star hotel.* One day at the breakfast we have been given a table next to the terrace, ordered the coffee, picked up some food and when we came back they had given our table to another guest who arrived after us... They apologized and proposed another table, but that does not make you feel very special.* We were supposed to arrive at 5am and the plane was late 1 hour. I had booked an hotel pick-up, having read that they had nice BMW 7 Series with fresh towels and drinks on arrival. In practice nobody was waiting to greet us neither before nor after the passport control. We had to go to the hotel counter at the airport to get the guy popping up. Instead of BMW 7 Series we got a Lexus 350 with no towels nor drinks, charged 150 UAD vs. 60 UAD for a metered taxi. Overall good hotel with good facilities but with a lot of hick-ups in the service and a bad/unreliable internet access. Next time I would rather try the One&amp;Only (we had a dinner there and the place is just gorgeous - definitely another level than the GH or Le Royal Meridien).	
May 6 2009 	Great hotel great staff minutes to everything...	My wife and I stayed at Grosvenor House West Marina for 5 nights as part of a stopover returning from the Maldives on our honeymoon. This was the finest hotel we had ever stayed in! We stayed in a Royal Club Room on the 13th floor. The room was spotless and the bed was the most comfortable ever! The breakfast that is included with the club rooms is phenominal! The happy hour also included from 6-8pm was also world class on the 44th floor overlooking the palm island. Special recognition to Joan who was a server at the bar happy hour. She was amazing and so friendly. Our glasses were never empty :) The hotel is situated in an area that is developing but we never heard any noise as other reviews stated. We slept like babies because the bed was so comfortable. The hotel is a short taxi ride to the Atlantis (Aquaventure a must), Bar Barasti (Great club/bar), Mall of Emirates (Ski Dubai), and quite a few restaurants. We paid no more than 20 dirham per taxi ride - very cheap!!! The only complaint I have is that the Buddah Bar didn't communicate well with the front desk at the Grosvenor House. On our last night there, we made a reservation and instead of given a table, we were escorted to the 2nd level where we were seated with others. We were on our honeymoon! We thought a reservation meant a reservation for a table for 2 - not a couch for 10. The issue was resolved after a bit of complaining but the Buddah Bar staff blamed the hotel for overbooking and said it happend quite often. Aside from that very small blemish, the stay was world class and we'd most definitely return, hopefully next year!	
May 3 2009 	How a real 5 star hotel should be	GH is the sister hotel to Le Royal Meridian and the two are connected by a free shuttle bus. Guests can make use of the facilities at the LRM (which I also stayed in) and I would recommend people reading my review of the LRM as well.GH is situated in New Dubai and as a result is currently sitting in the middle of a construction site. I stayed in a corner premier room with the biggest balcony I've seen in my life... well for a hotel at least. Unfortunately the noise of the construction once outside was intolerable and therefore you could not use the balcony for the noise and dust from the construction. I was there during a weekday so don't know what it would be like at the weekend when construction slows down.The hotel is well served by taxis but it's not really possible to walk anywhere as the construction makes the crossing of the road even more challenging. I'd recommend taking the free shuttle to LRM and then you will have access to all the amenities as well as the opportunity to go to the Walk for food, etc.We ate in the hotel lobby. The two light meals were not cheap (around 50GBP for two) but the food was of exceptional quality and the service was well honed. I was particularly impressed by the service of the breakfast staff who made every efforts to remember my name from one day to the next. After staying at the LRM for the earlier two days I have to say that the service at GH was much better in that staff truely could anticipate needs, weren't over bearing and knew how to keep people happy.The premier hotel room was large and featured a full size bath and separate shower, as well as the aforementioned huge balcony. The noise was not too much of a problem with the door shut and while we face the waterfront the views weren't as good as LRM.I would say that the GH is very much more geared to the business traveller rather than the family like LRM. There's a very nice bakery downstairs of the hotel and a nice surprise in the room was a fresh delivery of a baked good each day. There was also complimentary water but this was not as plentiful as LRM. However, you can always pick more up at the gym at LRM. A nice touch was also a special welcome gift of a candle and bath salts which was a nice gift to take home.The night turn down service was efficient and left a candle burning in the bathroom. For some strange reason the air conditioning was a bit over zealous which means that it turned itself on when you left the room. This meant the room was very cool when returning to the room (perhaps good for some people) but I prefer my rooms to be at room temperature. There probably was some way to turn it off but since I was only there for a couple of nights I didn't bother checking.The breakfast selection was wider than the fushion restaurant at LRM and while the exclusivity may not be there it made up in choice. Food was of high quality and worthy of a 5 star rating.Overall an exceptional stay and service at GH. I would recommend for business travellers particularly those who may need to be near New Dubai. Those with families are better off staying at the sister LRM which is on the beach.The service and staff will stand out in my memory for this stay. The only real downside is the noise outside which meant the balcony could not be used and the location meaning that access to the beach had to be via mini-bus rather than foot.	
