Apr 20 2009 	Excellent Hotel 	My husband and I stayed at this hotel in early April, arriving late on a Saturday night and departing in the afternoon on Tuesday. As I read in previous reviews, the service is really excellent. There are always staff there to open doors, take your luggage, welcome you and surprisingly, everyone seems genuinely friendly. We were promptly checked-in, our bags were brought up. Our only complaint, which I already mentioned to the hotel, is that there are literally like 15 different lights in the room and I don't know if it was just us, but it's nearly impossible to figure out which switch goes with which light. After turning off all the switches, lights were still on and it was kind of a pain with all the little lamps with individual switches.The room was very nice, clean, updated, nice decor. The bathroom was large, plus I loved that they had a separate mirror over the drawers so that I could apply my make up while my husband was over the sink area. Only one sink though, I always like when there are 2. The bath products were nice, as were the towels and robes.We went to Buddha Bar the first night for some drinks, not cheap, but nowhere in Dubai will you find cheap drinks. We also used the pool are one day, unfortunately when we came out about 3pm, the pool was completely shady (and it actually wasn't that hot outside!), but there is a side area where they move chairs. The staff was excellent, set up the chairs, brought a drink menu immediately, etc. We also went up to Bar 44 which is really impressive with great views.We did not eat at any of the restaurants in the hotel, nor did we get spa treatments and one of the main reasons for this is because this hotel does not participate in Starwood Preferred Guest program, like other Starwoods. We knew this before we stayed, but were really disappointed by this. Usually we'd eat at the restaurants, get treatments and other hotel extras, but because we weren't getting any points, we went elsewhere for this stuff.We were told after the fact that we had gotten some extra treats in our room and I'm not sure if we actually got the normal room upgraded that someone of our spg level does, but the room was nice regardless. Every afternoon, fruit and little candies were left in the room and they always replenished the water for free, which was much appreciated. It's too bad though, because we didn't know if any of these things were extra or if they were what everyone else gets. I think in other hotels they leave a note saying 'compliments of Starwood Preferred' for example.We debated over the hotel, whether to stay at the Le Meridien or the Sheraton Jumeriah, and finally decided on this hotel because of the price and the reviews. We were heading to the Maldives after, so we decided it wasn't a big deal to stay at the beach. The location was fine and taxis are cheap in Dubai, I guess the only problem is that there is so much construction right around the hotel, that you really can't walk anywhere. There's a great shopping centre with lots of restaurants about 5 minutes from the hotel, but there's no way you could walk there with the construction. Luckily there's a shuttle that goes often from the hotel to the Le Meridien and then you can walk from there (it's really close). We found this very convenient. The construction didn't bother us at all, and literally construction is everywhere, but if you want to be able to walk directly from your hotel, then maybe the Le Meridien is better.We took the private car service to the airport and this was good. I'm sure it's more expensive than a cab, but it's a nice car and the driver is friendly.We also found the concierge very helpful. We wanted to see a movie one night and they looked up all the times and recommended a restaurant for us. Each day we were greeted by the concierge and they were really great.We also used the free services in the spa area, jacuzzi, steam room, sauna, etc and this area is very nice (it's separate for men and women).Overall our stay was excellent. The room was very nice, as were the other areas of the hotel and the staff was great. My main complaint that would possibly prevent me from staying here again was the fact that it does not participate in the Starwood Preferred Guest program.	
