Apr 8 2009 	First class hotel and excellent value	My partner and I have just returned from a week at Grosvenor House and can't recommend it highly enough. The hotel itself is impeccable, impressive and luxurious. Every day the car park was filled with lamborghinis and ferraris which gives an indication of its grandeur - the hotel could very easily be pretentious and imposing but the staff are so friendly and attentive, they make this wonderful space a warm and welcoming home from home. The breakfast couldn't be better and for those that want pool / beach, simply hop on the shuttle bus across the road and enjoy first class facilities and service at the Royal Meridian. Perhaps one of the best things about this hotel is that there are two great bars on site - I wouldn't say nightlife is Dubai's strong point so if you want a good time - day and night - it would be hard to beat a stay at the Grosvenor. We went for drinks in another 3 hotels (including Atlantis and Burj Al Arab) and found nothing to beat GH in terms of ambiance and value. The spa is also brilliant and was never crowded. There is building right next door - but it's Dubai - expect cranes!. The building didn't affect our holiday one bit. If we go back, we'll head straight for GH.	
