Apr 2 2009 	Disappointing	This was our 3rd stay at the Grosvenor and we came away disappointed. It was a series of niggles that combined to make this a less then enjoyable stay.We emailed the hotel in advance of checking in, requesting spa and restaurant reservations and a Club room overlooking the Marina to ensure we were not disturbed by the building of the new Grosvenor tower. On arrival, no mention was made of a request for a room on the Marina side and we were given a room at the front. We were even asked if we had been to Dubai before so obviously no-one bothers to make notes of returning guests – perhaps they feel they do not need repeat business.The Club lounge was far too busy in the evenings which meant that staff were running around trying to attend to everyone but forgetting orders. The afternoon tea menu never changed and the evening canapés were on a rotation every couple of days. If you are here for more than 4 days it gets extremely boring.Previously, in Club rooms you also received little afternoon canapés in room but apart from a couple of occasions, this time it was slices of cake which were dry and tired and had been seen that morning on the breakfast buffet. We were also forgotten altogether on 2 days as was our room cleaning which despite a request had still not been done 4 hours later.Several problems with Wireless access as well as faults with the TV computer in our room. The computer was finally replaced although this took several reminders to staff.Ottomans restaurant had extremely pleasant and helpful staff but you could not justify the cost for a grilled kebab which is basically nothing more than you can buy in one of the numerous Malls.Gary Rhodes, staff were over familiar and the Maitre D insisted he knew my husband even though he had never visited before so then tried to insist he knew him from London. It was all somewhat embarrassing especially as he then spent the rest of the evening taking great pains to avoid our table. The food was good but if you want the Rhodes experience visit one of his London restaurants where the staff are more professional and amazingly the bill will be cheaper. So nothing major but this used to be an excellent hotel and it has now slipped into the ok bracket. Guests were wearing skimpy shorts at both breakfast and dinner – we used to come here precisely to avoid the Benidorm crowd. I am sure if you have never stayed here before then you will think it is fine but with so many new hotels opening, we will now look to somewhere different to provide the experience we used to get at the Grosvenor.	
