Mar 14 2009 	Great Hotel Great Service	We stayed here in March 2009 for 5 nights with our 18 month old daughter and we have to say it was one of the best hotels we have stayed in. We we're in a one bed appartment which was clean and spacious and had a small kitchen which was handy with the little one. The room was cleaned everyday and fresh fruit provided. As part of the room, you have access to the Grosvernor Club Lounge which is a real treat. However, just note that you are not able to use this if you have an child - it's access for adults only. However, we were able to make full use of the evening conplimentary drinks in the Leaves bar with the baby. The service was exceptional and nothing is too much trouble. All the staff were happy to help and were always great with our daughter. We never had to wait for the shuttle to the Le Royal Meridian (max 5-10mins away) and we have to say that although the pool at the Grosvernor is really nice, with the baby we found the pool at the Royal Meridian much better. There is alot of building work around the hotel (not unusual for the whole of Dubai!) but we never heard it in our room, particularly at night. The only problem is though that it is difficult to walk around to the Marina restaurants as some of the pavements are closed off. There is a regular shuttle to the Mall of Emirates everyday which is handy in the evenings for something to do. There is a children's play area there which we found great to entertain the baby for an hour or so. This was an all round superb hotel with everything you could possibly want in a 5 star. It exceeded our expectations and we will definately be returning soon!	
