Feb 22 2009 	Great views and nice rooms	Stayed for a few nights in Feb. Check in was fast, and a receptionist walks you to your room and shows you all the features, which is always a nice touch. The room featured contemporary decor and was a little on the small side (34sqm from memory) but had a nice balcony with a great view of the beach and harbour below and was spotless. There was also an outdoor table and chairs which is a great way to enjoy the view. There's construction next door where they are building its twin tower, so it can be noisy at times but with the windows and balcony door shut it shouldnt be an issue. The bed was comfy but the pillows were as soft as marshmallows. There's a 42in plasma and about 60 channels, along with a PC based DVD player. No tv in the bathroom though, and the shower cubile might be a little cramped for those who are generously built. Bvlgari toiletries are always nice but dont forget to bring your own toothbrush. Lighting, a/c and housekeeping are all controled through a touch pad console which can be fiddly to use. Although the hotel isnt located in the CBD, taxis are cheap and plentiful, and there is always a big queue of them outside the hotel, which is invaluable as this wasnt the case for a lot of other hotels. Daily fruit and chocs was a nice touch, but housekeeping never replenished the teabags which although trivial was annoying, especially since the minibar was constantly topped up. On checkout I didnt check the bill properly and was charged for stuff i didnt consume from the minibar. When I emailed the hotel they eventually said theyd reverse the charge, but never did. No big deal since its a trivial amount but at the same time its irritating to be overcharged and unprofessional to renege.There's a cosy bar at the top floor of the hotel with nice views and the much hyped Buddha bar is right next door, so if you get blind drunk in the wee hours of the morning its only a short walk to sleep it off.The staff were friendly, the lobby ritzy, and the room was comfortable and quite plush without being OTT. A very nice place to stay and can be excellent value at the right rate. Its location is close to JBR and the Marina which has some nice restaurants and most Malls are 10-15 mins away.	
