Jan 18 2009 	Great Hotel Good Service - Location still a noisy construction zone	To start - this is a positive review. It is a great hotel with good service, high quality food, great rooms and I would go back - but probably on business rather than as a holiday location for the next couple of years until the construction is complete.We stayed at Grosvenor knowing the state of the Marina - ie still a heavy construction zone. A new multi-lane roadbridge, Grosvenor House II and another high rise apartment block are being built within 100 metres of the hotel. Even so, on the 20th floor in a premier room the construction noise was very loud in our first room at 3 in the morning, which was bad because it was a work trip and I managed 2 hours sleep the first night before all day on the hoof.The hotel were good. They moved us without question and gave us a choice of different rooms. In the end we settled for an Apartment on the other side of the hotel on floor 39, which had a kitchen, dining table and lounge area and great views in to the marina, (rather than beach), as well as a guest toilet, master bathroom and bedroom. It was a really good room, far quieter and the only strange thing was that it had no separate shower cubicle. You could occaisionally hear some noise still though at night from the building sites. I would recommend anyone to ask for a very high floor room looking in to the marina on the other side to the Harbour Hotel until the construction is over. Our room rate came with lounge access which is a valuable perk at this property. On the 44th floor the lounge is open from 0600 through 2200 serving breakfast, refreshments, afternoon tea and drinks / snacks, all of which are complimentary. Comparing Sloane's and the 44th Lounge for breakfast, I recommend the lounge. Its smaller, quieter and whilst there is less choice (especially of cooked foods), the service is more attentive and more personalised. If you are leaving early though and back late, or on vacation and fancy a pre-dinner glass of champagne watching the sun go down, then this is a great facility with friendly staff.The beach facilities at the sister hotel are OK and the shuttle is convenient (never waited more than about 10 minutes) on the weekend day that I used this, though I think that the beach / pool and service at Jumeriah Al Qasr / Dar Al Masayaf is far superior in this area. There are plenty of nice outside restaurants down the Jumeriah beach at The Walk and more and more emerging in the Marina, but there is still too much construction to be able to walk anywhere in the marina safely. We ate in both Ottomans and Indego and the food was excellent, as was the room service food - prices are not cheap, but no hotels in Dubai are ! So in summary - great, personalised service, but the marina is not finished, and if you are on vacation then beach facilities are better with zero consturction from the Palm / Marina at Madinat Jumeriah. So for now thumbs up as a business location, but be sure to check your room location and choose a package that includes Grosvenor Lounge access and Wifi to make for a good experience.	
