; drinking every night its great, but not much else to do. Having said that I was looking for a relaxing holiday with my wife, and thats EXACTLY what I got.BOOK early if you wish to visit the Burj Al Arab, you can do afternoon tea, its expensive but worth the effort, book before you travel, as they are booked weeks in advance 'busy season' try the MONKEY FREEZE cocktail , absolutely yummy.All in all ,my experince with Grosvenor was superb, would I go back again ? YES in a heartbeat... The hotel itself was sooo good, it made up for all the buiding and industry going on around it.The General Manager is a British Women, who obviously knows how to please her clients, this hotel will not disappoint you. This is the first time EVERY member of staff treated me with respect,and a professional attitude. i travel to many destinations every year, and NOTHING has come close to the service I got at the Grosvenor.I will be booking again in October 2008, thats how good it is.Paul Miles (room 1513.. excellent view) MAY 12th - May 19th 2008(hope this review helps you, I have tried to be honest and informative)	
