Jan 4 2008 	Good Hotel Lousy Location	Spent a week at the GH with my wife as a pre-Christmas sunshine break. It's a great time to go because it only gets up to about 30 degrees, however ladies should take a pash or a jacket cos it gets a little cool in the evening.On the whole I can't fault the hotel, it's a slick operation, nice decor, rooms comfortable but not very spacious for the money. Having done the research on Tripadvisor, I expected the shadows over the pool deck and a certain amount of building site noise. The shadows are solved by decamping to the Meridian via shuttle bus (very quick and virtually on-demand). The Meridian has a great pool and garden area with masses of loungers and pretty good bar service. Frankly, don't waste your time with the GH pool; the building site next door is relentless. We went every day to the Meridian, and it's much quieter there.Another tip; I paid and extra £400 for the week to upgrade to Club Ocean View. It was a 9th floor room with a balcony, but right up against the building site (an identical tower to the existing GH is going up, so that's the end of ocean views from the original building. The were pile-driving night and day so the balcony was unusable and it was noisy in the room even with all the drapes pulled. On the upside, its true that the Grosvenor Club on 44th floor free-pours champagne and serves masses of canapes. However, you need to be there by 6.15 (it opens at 6) otherwise you don't stand much chance of a seat once all the other freeloaders arrive! We did one night in there and then gave up trying!Taxis are cheap and plentiful, however Dubai is so spread out it can take ages to get somewhere if it's off Jumeirah Beach.On the shopping; we went to Mall of the Emirates (like Lakeside) and Bur Juman (hard to get to but very high standard). Trouble is, nothing worth buying appears to be any cheaper than UK. Designer labels seem to be fairly consistently priced world-wide and Dubai is no different. My wife reports there were some savings at Dune and Monsoon, those kind of stores if that is what you like.Given the choice, next time I would definitely stay at the Meridian rather than the GH (it was full when we booked), however on balance I think we'll give Dubai a miss until it's a bit nearer completion. In our opinion, the best bits of Thailand are better value and much more interesting. Recommend the Royal Wing in Pattaya for ultimate comfort and service.	
