Sep 8 2007 	Nice but flawed.	Have just returned from the Grosvenor where we stayed for 6 nights. I booked the hotel based on previous reviews and although cant knock the quality of the hotel cant help feeling a little disappointed at some of the major flaws the location had.Hotel facilities are what you would expect from a 5 star location. It is definitely designed for business travellers, I find sometimes this means an even better service than normal - staff could not do enough for you.The rooms were lovely, with great little extras (fresh rose delivered every night, lovely little canapes left in room etc). The bed was so comfortable, we wanted to bring it home!There were great restaraunts in the Hotel. We ate at Indigo which was top class, Ottomans, which was ok. Unfortunately Mezzanine was closed for refurb which we would have loved to have tried (saw Gary Rhodes who is opening Mezzanine when we left). Didnt like the constant push on the overpriced wine where there is obviously a big mark up.The Budda bar is great - a real hot spot and Bar 44 is excellent also - really pricey though - make sure you check the menu for prices. We had about 4 drinks each and the bill was £145!No matter how nice the hotel is, you cannot disguise the fact you are in the middle of a building site. Granted, when inside you cannot hear it but tried to sit on the balcony one afternoon to read (there is no view only a building site outside) and had to put my ipod on at full blast so couldnt hear the noise, which goes on all night.The pool area is very poor. As previous reviewers have mentioned, there are gawping builders from the local sites who have full view of the pool. It has been designed poorly so the sun is lost by mid afternoon. There is a shuttle over to the Meridian if you want to laze in the sun - they have full access to the beach and many pools where you are more private and cant hear the diggers! The Meridien has a fantastic Seafood restaraunt where we ate one night - you just pick your fresh fish and it is cooked to your liking - the Lobster was fantastic. After chatting to a someone staying in this hotel, I think the Grosvenor has better rooms but this hotel had better beach/pool facilities.Although the staff were great, we found the room interruptions a little intrusive at times. As we were getting ready for dinner (early evening) staff wanted to turn the beds etc. We had to turn them away on many occasions. This was not a major issue however, I have stayed in many hotels who establish you patterns of leaving the room (which were mostly the same every day) and try not to interrupt you. Despite my negative comments, we did enjoy our break and would return but believe there are many resorts that have everything the Grosvenor and The Meridien have combined.	
