May 29 2007	Second Time Around Not Quite So Impressed	Returned from a 10 day stay at GHH on Thursday 24th May.We booked this hotel for our second trip to Dubai as we were so impressed with it last September.However I have to stay we were not nearly so impressed this time, maybe due to High Expectations!!!!We went on HB Package as food in Sloanes last year was terrific. Big Mistake: Food Cold, Plates Cold and nowhere near the choice we had last year! I got terribly sick and am afraid to say it was definitely the food caused it. I didn't have nearly enough alcohol to cause the violent vommiting and scoots!We did complain and were told Sloanes currently did not have a Chef and the hotel was aware there was a problem with the food!In my opinion a 5 star hotel should always be on top of these problems.We had been upgraded to a suite on arrival which was very nice as we had a suite on our last stay as well, but on entering our suite on 36th floor we could both smell what could only be described as chip fat! Maybe the previous occupant had a good few takeaways. We soon discovered it was the bathrobes, one in the wardrobe and one in the bathroom. They seriously honked, and seeing as I unpacked so did our clothes placed in the wardrobe. Housekeeping were called and soon whisked the offending bathrobes away and replaced them. Mind you one of the replacements had a tissue stuck in the lining of the sleeve and we now know the robes given on your first day are the ones you have for your full stay!!!! I always managed to get the one with the tissue up the sleeve!Next comes the building work which we were well aware of from our last stay but found it to be much more intrusive this time. Concrete Mixers would line up outside around 11 pm every night and carry on throughout the night offloading and returning with more. On one evening we counted 10 lined up along the road!We could hear the reversing beepers all through the night, although we were looking directly into the building site and the panels on our windows would creak with the racket that was going on outside.Club Lounge was packed on most occasions as we were sent across to Bar 44 a few times. But that was no problem. The biggest laugh we had out of our 10 nights here was when the waiter in the Club Lounge told us one morning at Breakfast they had no teaspoons!!!! He proceeded to tell everyone who came in until he was taken round the corner and given a good telling off!Well these are my gripes and please excuse me if you think I am being a bit harsh on the hotel but if you look back to my review last year we couldn't compliment the place enough and we were disappointed this time!My advice is to go B/B or R/O as the hotel is still very beautiful and most of the staff ensure your stay is as comfortable and relaxed as possible. Beds and Bedlinen are very exclusive and the Bulgari toiletries go down a treat. Keep away from the rooms that overlook Habtoor and LRM as the building work is going on between GHH and the two hotels mentioned. I think the view is going to be very restricted when the buildings are complete.Well sorry if I have annoyed anyone with my review but I had to point out the bad bits.Will we return to Duba? Yes we will but not to GHH. Next time we will stay at the beach or in the City	
