 them are very good. They are not cheap but high quality. Believe me, if it comes to food I am really choicy. I was also thrilled not only by the standard of the food but also by the tableware in every restaurant - so stylish!! And the little touches if you just orderd a drink or a coffee - always it came with something extra. If you like sweets you will immediately gain two kilos just because you cant resist!The service in the restaurants is good and very friendly but not comparable with the standard you are used to in exquisite restaurantsin Austria for example but that we also did not expect. I tried the Gym which is well equipped and has a nice view of the pool. The Spa is nice but a little bit small. I went to the sauna butthere were not enough beds to rest.It seemed to us that the GH currently is the hot spot in Dubai. The Budda bar, the restaurants and the bar on the top floor seem to attract very trendy people and one night we just stood in front of hotel to watch the very expensive cars arriving. We were almost a little bit ashamed when AVIS delivered our Peugot we rented for a view days ;-) No, seriously we never felt uncomfortable in GH withouta big car and beeing dressed up. All in all a very nice experience for a view days although not cheap.For a better price think about the Al Manzil, only 4 star rated but brand new and in a very nice modern arabian style (be aware of the open style bathroom - not everybody likes that). Altough I hate buffets - there it was amazing.This was my first trip to Dubai and I will maybe go again in 10 years or so after the construction is mostly finished....but who knows what they plan next.	
