Mar 5 2007 	Fab Hotel.	Fab Hotel. The staff here are excellent, they can't do enough for you.The club room is definitely worth going for. The access it gives you to the club lounge on the 44th floor is a great way to start your evening. You can have any drinks you want, and there are a selection of hot and cold canapes to enjoy also. It can get full between 7-730pm, so try and get in sharpish. Breakfast can also be taken here, but I would recommend Sloanes, there is a fantastic selection. The dinner buffet in Sloanes is pretty good too, Indego the Indian restaurant is excellent. There are little added extras of fruit and cakes delivered to your room every day.If you do book a club room this gives you complimentary return airport transfers, in a BMW 7 series. Just call the hotel concierge a few days in advance to book. Unfortunately the other comments about the pool and building work are true. The sun gets blocked out early afternoon, you can move to a small suntrap if you want to say, but if you are looking for a full day by the pool, we found it far better to go to the Meridien across the road. The pool and grounds are lovely there, and it's right on the beach. They do a pretty good cocktail too. Try the beach restaurant at the Habtoor next door for lunch.If you book the GHH you won't be disappointed.	
