Feb 1 2007	Stay here if you love luxury!	My husband and i have just returned from a weeks holiday in Dubai and thanks to all the previous reviews on this site we chose the GH and we weren't disappointed. We decided to book a club room which gave us access to the club level of the hotel and when we arrived (after our FOC airport transfer in a private limo, fab touch) it only got better as we were upgraded to an apartment suite on the 34th floor. It was huge, with a large living area and bedroom and with views down to the Burj that were to die for, especially at night. Everything was immaculate and there was always fresh fruit, water and little extras brought to our room daily. The staff were amazingly attentive and efficient and went out of their way to make sure that you had everything you needed at all times. One point to note if you do go for a club level room is to take advantage of the breakfast at Sloanes rather than in the club room itself as the breakfast options there are minimal compared to those at Sloanes, and for no extra charge. As other reviewers have noted the pool area is overlooked by building work, but surprisingly it's not actually that intrusive or noisy. There is also the bonus of complimentary cold fruit and bottled water which is a nice touch. If you prefer the beach though, the Royal Meredien (GH's sister hotel) is right across the road and there's a free shuttle that runs to it every 5 mins. As well as the beach there are several pools and beautifully landscaped gardens to relax in, but it's a much larger and more impersonal hotel and we were always glad to come back to the GH at the end of the day. We had a fantastic trip made all the more special by staying in this amazing hotel, i can not recommend it enough.	
