r this, but I would recommend the Lebanese BBQ restaurant (the name fails me). Delicious.The hotel pampered to every wish we had. The evening turn down service was special and so was sitting in the living room watching the sun set over the gulf.It was my wifes birthday whilst we were there. Upon arrival from the beach we were greated with a bottle of wine on ice &amp; a birthday cake. What a very nice touch.The only downside is that the building work is immense, but no part of Dubai has escaped this. You don't notice it in the hotel or on the beach. My only concern is over development. The view from the hotel is amazing, it would be a shame to plonk a high rise in between it and the beach.On the whole I would recommend this hotel and I will be going back to stay, hopefully not to far into the future.	
