Nov 6 2006 	Fantastic Rooms; Buddha Bar is a Must	July isn't the best time of year to go to Dubai, but my wife and I were looking for a weekend away from Doha. We booked a room at GH, and when they found out it was our anniversary, they upgraded us to a better room/small suite. I don't know if I have stayed in a better room...enormous bathroom, incredibly comfortable bed, two flat screen TVs, all lights/tvs/AC on a remote control. I could go on and on, but you really need to see it for yourself.Another plus is that the hotel is connected to the famous Buddha Bar Restaurant / Lounge. We had been planning on just doing drinks there (dinner elsewhere), but on the recommendations of several friends, we decided to dinner as well. We were not disappointed, as it was the best dinner of our trip. A bit on the expensive side, but the food was great and the atmosphere more than made up for the cost. If you have drinks upstairs, avoid the champagne cocktails (not much to write home about and very expensive) and instead go straight for the blueberry mojito. A fine beverage...	
Nov 3 2006 	Superb!	We have just returned from a week at Grosvenor House Hotel and just wanted everyone to know how fantastic it is. The reviews you see on these and other pages are no exaggeration. Upon arrival at the airport we greeted by a chauffeur in a hotel car. We were provided with water and cold towels to freshen up (it is hot, even after a couple of minutes you will be very grateful for these). Upon arrival at the hotel, the lobby is extremely impressive. Our luggage was whisked away and our check-in was completely hassle free. The hotel has got a fantastic range of restaurants –check our Mezzanine for the best dinner in Dubai. Food was outstanding in all restaurants. Definitely consider staying in a club room/suite. You get access tot eh club lounge on 44th Floor with the most spectacular views of the sea and the Palm. Drinks and canapés are served daily 6-8pm and are commentary (this will be a welcome relief to your wallet as Dubai is not cheap).The Dubai Marina is stunning by day and night. Looking out at night from Bar 44 the views are as good as anything in Manhattan/Honk Kong/Tokyo. I cannot recommend this hotel highly enough. Be warned there is a lot of construction but you do not notice inside the hotel/from your room. You will hear it by the pool (which becomes shaded in the afternoon) but it is not too bothersome. It can be escaped by visiting the pool complex of the sister hotel with all the other sun worshippers. Must do: Desert Safari by jeep. Miss: Burj Al Arab – most exquisitely expensive bad taste I’ve ever seen. (We stayed there for our final night and left wishing we hadn’t)	
