und the gold souk area and haggle. We travelled in August which is there low season due to the very hot weather however not unberable and less busy which makes it more posssible for upgrades etc, email the hotels if celebrating birthdays etc and i promise you they will spoil you rottern. All the hotels are stunning and apart from the Burj Arab which is a real wallet breaker then the Grovsner house must be one of the top hotels in Dubai i cant speak highley enough about it, however the Mina A Salam is also amazing and right next to the Burj Arab so check that out too.	
